 the charge. The Judge, Mr Salihu Ibrahim, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N200,000 with one surety in like sum. He, thereafter, adjourned the case until Nov. 25 for hearing. Vanguard A teenager, Yusuf Obaka, who allegedly kidnapped a 17-year-old girl, on Wednesday appeared in a Grade I Area Court in Mpape, Abuja. The police charged Obaka, 18, who lives in Mpape area, Abuja, with criminal conspiracy, and kidnapping The Prosecutor, Mr Stanley Nwaforaku, told the court that one Joseph Ogbecheâ€¦ November 20, 2019 In "News" A 27-year-old housewife, Stella Okeke, who allegedly stole breast pads and other beauty from a supermarket, on Wednesday appeared in an Upper Area Court in Mpape, Abuja. June 19, 2019 In "News" TWO days after the Monday, January 31 murder of Mrs. Nonye Doris Okere allegedly by a policeman at Mpape, Abuja, the Inspector-General of Police (IGP), Mr. Hafiz Ringim, directed that a criminal suit be instituted against the suspect. February 19, 2011 In "Metro"